    <h1>Basil-Infused Olive Oil & Smoked Paprika Blend Delight</h1>
    <p>Indulge in this gourmet delight that combines the aromatic essence of basil-infused olive oil with the smoky allure of a special smoked paprika blend. This recipe elevates everyday ingredients to a whole new level, offering a burst of flavors that will tantalize your taste buds.</p>

    <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons basil-infused olive oil</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon smoked paprika blend</li>
        <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Instructions:</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).</li>
        <li>Place the chicken breasts on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.</li>
        <li>Drizzle the basil-infused olive oil over the chicken breasts, ensuring they are evenly coated.</li>
        <li>Sprinkle the smoked paprika blend, salt, and pepper over the chicken breasts, rubbing the seasonings gently to cover both sides.</li>
        <li>Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through and golden on the outside.</li>
        <li>Let the chicken rest for a few minutes before serving.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="tips">
        <h3>Chef's Tips:</h3>
        <p>For an extra burst of flavor, drizzle a little more basil-infused olive oil over the chicken just before serving. It will enhance the dish with its fresh, herbal notes.</p>
        <p>If you're grilling the chicken instead of baking, brush the basil-infused olive oil on the chicken while grilling to create a tantalizing aroma.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="serving">
        <h3>Serving Suggestions:</h3>
        <p>Pair this delectable chicken dish with a fresh salad drizzled with a simple vinaigrette made with basil-infused olive oil and a splash of balsamic vinegar for a complete gourmet experience.</p>
    </div>
</body>
